# Auto Documentation & Diagram Audit

## When This Runs

1. **After every plan execution** (referenced from `auto-execute-plans.mdc`)
2. **After any modification touching 3+ files** in `bin/core/`, `bin/api/`, or `prompts/`

## Skip Conditions

Do NOT run this audit if changes are **exclusively** in:
- `testing/` (test-only changes rarely affect architecture diagrams)
- `ui/` (frontend changes don't affect backend diagrams)
- `docs/` (documentation-only changes)
- `.cursor/` (rule/config changes)

If changes span both skippable and non-skippable paths, run the audit.

